WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
Meet VayuChat on Android: a private air-quality analyst powered by a small Gemma model.

00:07.000 --> 00:12.200
The airplane icon is on, and the app has no internet permission.

00:12.200 --> 00:22.500
Ask which city had the highest average PM2.5 in 2023. Gemma returns a compact, constrained function plan.

00:22.500 --> 00:32.500
Kotlin validates the city, pollutant, date, and operation, then executes it over 146,459 ground-measurement records.

00:32.500 --> 00:42.500
The same pipeline can return a dataframe or a native scatter plot.

00:42.500 --> 00:51.700
The model handles language. Deterministic code does the math. Every answer can be reviewed and audited.

00:51.700 --> 00:55.000
VayuChat runs on Android, iPhone, and the hosted research app.
